<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="S" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Soil2" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Soil,</orth> subst. stain, tarnish, blemish: <bibl n="shak. mm 5.141" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. V, 141</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ado 3.2.5" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado III, 2, 5</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 2.47" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL II, 47</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 2.47" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL II, 47</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 2h4 4.5.190" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B IV, 5, 190</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 1.2.26" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 I, 2, 26</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 2.2.148" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. II, 2, 148</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 4.1.56" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 1, 56</bibl> (Ff <emph>soilure</emph>). <bibl n="shak. jc 1.2.42" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. I, 2, 42</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 1.3.15" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. I, 3, 15</bibl>. In <bibl n="shak. ant 1.4.24" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. I, 4, 24</bibl> some M. Edd. <emph>--s</emph> (a plural not used by Sh.), O. Edd. <emph>foils.</emph>
